            "Body": "After finding a nice tree, you're ready to move on to your next stage and make a nice chrysalis for yourself. You deserve the rest. <br><br> Everything feels still. The rustle of leaves, the hum of chatter—it’s all behind me now. I remember the sweet tang of mulberry, the warmth of the sun on my back, the way laughter felt when I made my first friend. I was just a caterpillar, inching through life. I didn't know I was preparing for something more. It’s quiet here, but not empty. I’m not afraid. I’m changing. I think I’m ready to fly.",
